      "content": "Keeping items as 'in stock' when our warehouse data suggests otherwise can lead to diminished customer trust once the discrepancy becomes apparent. Honesty in our listings protects our brand's reputation and upholds customer loyalty. Leveraging the 'in stock' status only for a short while may lead to a temporary increase in sales, but the potential long-term damage from disappointed customers can have a far more severe impact on sales and our reputation. Instead, consider implementing a 'low stock' alert system to inform customers and give us an opportunity to gather backorders in the interim. Plus, providing updated estimated delivery dates or offering customers a discount or credit for items not in stock can be a beneficial compromise, retaining customer interest and maintaining sales momentum.",
